HEADWORD: Zantewood
<hw>Zan"te*wood`</hw> <pr>(?)</pr>, <pos>n.</pos> <fld>(Bot.)</fld>
<sd>(a)</sd> <def>A yellow dyewood; fustet; -- called also
<altname>zante</altname>, and <altname>zante fustic</altname>. See
<er>Fustet</er>, and the Note under <er>Fustic</er>.</def> <sd>(b)</sd>
<def>Satinwood (<spn>Chloroxylon Swietenia</spn>).</def>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><ent>Zantiot</ent>⟦br⟧
